While Drew is searching for Emma in Hell, Emma herself discovers that she hasn't been travelling through dimensions, but through time in one true dimension. After a short adventure in Hell, Drew and Emma are reunited in New Mexico.
Last issue.

True fact- fabled pirate Jean Lafitte spent his last years not on the high seas, but in Texas. Guess who his best friend was? Jim Bowie. What adventures must a swashbuckling corsair and an American frontiersman have had together in the Old West? It's Deadwood with pirates, man. Pirates!

description:
1. Blue Beetle:  The Blue Beetle stands off against the mad scientist Dr. Krako who can animate skeletons.  The undead takes over the city and it is up to the Blue Beetle to stop Krako in this eighteen page adventure.
  2. Samson: Professor Zarr has kidnapped David and plans on using his new Z-Ray on him but Samson steps in to save the day in this thirteen page story.
  3. Flame: Doctor Drool is brought back from the dead to have his vengeance on the fourteen men who had him executed.  He manages to kill a few of them before the Flame stops him once and for all....or did he?  This is a fifteen page story.
  4. Raider Squadron: A short story of a navel/air battle against the Nazi's.  This is not a comic.  This is a two page story.
  5. Samson: Samson and David take out another mad man bent on global domination in south America. In this thirteen page story Samson destroys every means for making war in the matter of a day.
name: Raider Squadron

description:
1. Blue Beetle: The Blue Beetle fights the Condor., but Mike Mannigan rescues the girl in this fifteen page feature.
  2. Samson and David:  Samson and David track down the Wasp but it is J. Rembrandt Speedball who finds out who he is in the fifteen page story
  3. Flame:  The Flame, Pug, and Linda Dale stop some Nazi's from blowing up an American plant and slowing American production.  This is a fifteen page feature.
  4. Wings over Albania: This is a two page short story not a comic.  It is about a air battle in World War II in Albania involving The Canadian Air Force.
  5. Blue Beetle:  The Blue Beetle stops some thugs in the twelve page feature.
name: Wings over Albania
